Class ModulesFileModelGeneratorSymbolic

  • java.lang.Object
    • simulator.ModulesFileModelGeneratorSymbolic
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ModelGenerator, ModelGeneratorSymbolic, ModelInfo

    public class ModulesFileModelGeneratorSymbolic
extends java.lang.Object
implements ModelGeneratorSymbolic
    A variant of ModulesFileGenerator that is suitable for model generation at a symbolic level, i.e., where numeric values are kept as expressions instead of being evaluated.
    Used by the parametric / exact engine to build models.
    Uses exact arithmetic to evaluate the various expressions in a model description.

      • getTransitionAction

        public java.lang.String getTransitionAction(int index)
                                     throws PrismException
        Description copied from interface: ModelGenerator
        Get the action label of a transition, specified by its index. The label can be any Object, but will often be treated as a string, so it should at least have a meaningful toString() method implemented. Absence of an action label is denoted by null. Note: For most types of models, the action label will be the same for all transitions within the same nondeterministic choice, so it is better to query the action by choice, not transition.
        Specified by:
        getTransitionAction in interface ModelGenerator
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • getTransitionAction

        public java.lang.String getTransitionAction(int index,
                                            int offset)
                                     throws PrismException
        Description copied from interface: ModelGenerator
        Get the action label of a transition within a choice, specified by its index/offset. The label can be any Object, but will often be treated as a string, so it should at least have a meaningful toString() method implemented. Absence of an action label is denoted by null. Note: For most types of models, the action label will be the same for all transitions within the same nondeterministic choice (i.e. for each different value of offset), but for Markov chains this may not necessarily be the case.
        Specified by:
        getTransitionAction in interface ModelGenerator
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • getChoiceAction

        public java.lang.String getChoiceAction(int index)
                                 throws PrismException
        Description copied from interface: ModelGenerator
        Get the action label of a choice, specified by its index. The label can be any Object, but will often be treated as a string, so it should at least have a meaningful toString() method implemented. Absence of an action label is denoted by null. Note: If the model has different actions for different transitions within a choice (as can be the case for Markov chains), this method returns the action for the first transition. So, this method is essentially equivalent to getTransitionAction(i, 0).
        Specified by:
        getChoiceAction in interface ModelGenerator
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • rewardStructHasTransitionRewards

        public boolean rewardStructHasTransitionRewards(int i)
        Description copied from interface: ModelInfo
        Returns true if the reward structure with index i defines transition rewards. (indexed from 0, not from 1 like at the user (property language) level) If this returns false, the model checker is allowed to ignore them (which may be more efficient). If using an algorithm or implementation that does not support transition rewards, you may need to return false here (as well as not defining transition rewards).
        Specified by:
        rewardStructHasTransitionRewards in interface ModelInfo
